    • Method Detail

      • queueCopyOfKeyEvent

        public void queueCopyOfKeyEvent(android.view.KeyEvent keyEvent)
        Queues a KeyEventInfo, wich is a copy of the specified KeyEvent, for later processing.
        The event will be recycled when processKeyInput() is called.
        Parameters:
        keyEvent - KeyEvent.

      • processKeyInput

        public void processKeyInput()
        Processes key input.
        This method should be called when the game updates, before the update is processed. If a key event has happened, this method will call KeyEventProcessor.processKeyEvent(KeyEventInfo).

      • onBackPressed

        public void onBackPressed()
        This method is called when the back button is pressed and there is no KeyEventProcessor set in this KeyProcessor.
        Finishes the Activity referenced by this KeyProcessor.

        public void setKeyEventProcessor(KeyEventProcessor keyEventProcessor)
